24:46.694 --> 24:48.104
Do it.

24:48.737 --> 24:49.726
[GUNSHOTS]

24:49.905 --> 24:51.770
I'll call Rat.

24:51.949 --> 24:53.064
[PHONE BEEPS]

24:54.410 --> 24:56.150
[PHONE RINGING]

24:58.247 --> 25:01.034
That's gotta be him.
Yeah.

25:03.335 --> 25:04.871
Hello.

25:10.676 --> 25:11.756
TYLER:
That's T.O.

25:15.681 --> 25:17.387
[ENGINE STARTS]

25:18.017 --> 25:21.225
That was Chibs, I gotta head to St. Thomas.
Could use some help.

25:21.395 --> 25:24.057
What about the thing with--?
RATBOY: It's gotta wait.

25:24.231 --> 25:27.143
Holy shit.
MAN: Come on.

25:30.863 --> 25:32.649
Now.

25:33.532 --> 25:35.113
Right there.

25:38.287 --> 25:40.118
Turn around.

25:41.415 --> 25:44.077
Samcro?
Yeah.

25:45.586 --> 25:47.793
How about that?

25:49.465 --> 25:50.671
[DING]

26:13.155 --> 26:14.520
[DOOR BEEPS]

26:49.984 --> 26:51.190
[BEEP]

27:39.950 --> 27:41.906
[WATER RUNNING]

27:57.343 --> 27:58.423
UNSER:
Looking for someone?

28:00.304 --> 28:02.260
Toss the gun.

28:02.806 --> 28:04.421
In the sink.

28:28.248 --> 28:29.533
[GROANS]

28:42.429 --> 28:44.590
Where was Eglee?

28:44.890 --> 28:47.677
First thing I did was move her
to another room.

28:47.976 --> 28:50.228
I didn't have time to call it in.

28:50.396 --> 28:53.684
How did you know Leland Gruen
was on his way to kill her?

28:54.400 --> 28:56.482
I got a heads-up.

28:56.902 --> 28:58.767
From who?

29:00.239 --> 29:01.854
Anonymous.

29:02.408 --> 29:04.524
Friends of Eglee's.

29:05.494 --> 29:09.863
You can't keep protecting them, Wayne.
This has got nothing to do with Tara.

29:10.916 --> 29:13.282
I gave my statement
to Carreira.

29:14.044 --> 29:15.659
It was a clean kill.

29:15.838 --> 29:18.921
We need you in there, LT.
Okay.

29:19.633 --> 29:23.842
We're not done. I'll talk to you later.
Yes, ma'am.

29:25.848 --> 29:29.432
I think your anonymous friends
are waiting for you in the lobby.

29:38.277 --> 29:39.938
Hey.

29:47.870 --> 29:49.201
[SIGHS]

29:49.955 --> 29:54.119
ls Eglee okay?
Yeah. Yeah.

29:56.962 --> 29:59.999
I put three bullets
in that man's chest.

30:00.174 --> 30:02.961
Hey, that guy was a scumbag.

30:03.135 --> 30:04.170
[PHONE RINGING]

30:04.344 --> 30:05.675
CHIBS:
Excuse me.

30:08.932 --> 30:10.843
You know how many kills I had
on the job?

30:11.310 --> 30:13.517
None.
That's right.

30:13.687 --> 30:17.350
Fired my weapon
maybe a dozen times.

30:17.524 --> 30:20.937
Two wounded perps. That's it.

30:21.570 --> 30:23.902
Does that tell you something, son?
Huh?

30:24.072 --> 30:25.778
About what's happening here?

30:25.949 --> 30:28.531
You said Eglee wasn't gonna talk.
She told the DA...

30:28.702 --> 30:31.318
...it was a few white guys
with Nazi ink.

30:31.497 --> 30:33.283
She didn't ID anybody.

30:33.457 --> 30:34.663
They didn't know that.

30:35.626 --> 30:38.368
They? The AB?

30:39.963 --> 30:42.955
Does that mean there's more coming?
No.

30:43.133 --> 30:44.634
Leland was the end of it.

30:48.555 --> 30:50.341
Thank you.

30:51.225 --> 30:52.305
I owe you.

30:55.145 --> 30:56.305
Yeah.

31:01.568 --> 31:02.853
Jackie.

31:03.028 --> 31:05.644
Was it Tyler?
No, Wendy.

31:05.822 --> 31:08.074
They need you at Abel's school.

31:08.242 --> 31:10.278
JAX: What now?
She doesn't know.

31:10.452 --> 31:12.864
Well, have her send Gemma.

31:13.747 --> 31:15.533
Child Services were called.

31:15.707 --> 31:17.789
They need the father.

31:22.256 --> 31:23.792
Go.

31:24.049 --> 31:27.007
We'll handle black.
You go and take care of your family.

31:28.428 --> 31:29.838
We got this, brother.

31:31.807 --> 31:33.513
All right. Yeah, all right.

31:35.102 --> 31:37.684
Hap, you stay with him.

31:41.108 --> 31:42.689
That's all we need.

31:53.787 --> 31:55.994
MOSES:
You saw what happened to Bobby.

31:56.164 --> 31:57.700
I carved out his eye.

31:58.292 --> 32:00.533
Cut his fingers off.

32:02.296 --> 32:04.628
That's what will happen
if you don't cooperate.

32:05.132 --> 32:08.795
So why don't we save ourself
the agony and time?

32:09.636 --> 32:13.504
Where is Samcro hiding
the pastor's son and wife?

32:24.443 --> 32:25.774
[RATBOY & T.O. GRUNTING]

32:40.083 --> 32:41.163
Jesus Christ.

32:46.256 --> 32:48.633
[FISTS THUMPING
AND RATBOY & T.O. GRUNTING]

32:49.968 --> 32:51.708
[DOOR BUZZING AND OPENS]

32:54.973 --> 32:56.679
From Tully.

33:23.085 --> 33:25.201
Holy shit.

33:41.937 --> 33:43.177
What the hell is going on?

33:44.064 --> 33:46.430
I don't know. They won't tell me shit.

33:46.608 --> 33:48.690
TREAL:
Are you Mr. Teller?

33:49.778 --> 33:51.109
Yeah.

33:51.279 --> 33:53.531
I'm the assistant principal,
Mildred Treal.

33:53.699 --> 33:56.441
And this is Investigator Shahid
from Child Services.

33:56.618 --> 33:58.825
Where's my kid? Is he okay?

33:59.246 --> 34:00.452
Yeah.

34:00.622 --> 34:02.829
Can you please just have a seat?

34:04.751 --> 34:06.707
SHAHID:
I'll go get Miss Harrison.

34:10.799 --> 34:12.414
Who's Miss Harrison?

34:12.592 --> 34:13.627
[GEMMA SCOFFS]

34:14.845 --> 34:16.676
Abel's nosy teacher.

34:18.640 --> 34:21.723
Can you at least tell us
why Child Services is here?

34:21.893 --> 34:23.394
TREAL:
We'll explain everything.

34:33.447 --> 34:36.905
Hey, buddy. What's going on?

34:38.535 --> 34:40.742
Show him, Abel.

34:47.127 --> 34:50.244
Jesus Christ.
Oh, my God, what happened, baby?

34:51.506 --> 34:52.837
Who did this to you?

34:56.094 --> 35:00.087
It's okay, honey, you can tell the truth.
This is a safe room.

35:00.682 --> 35:02.718
Who did this to you?

35:05.687 --> 35:07.018
Grandma.

35:33.048 --> 35:35.130
MOSES:
A grapefruit spoon...

35:35.300 --> 35:39.509
...turns out to be the perfect little tool
for taking out an eye.

35:40.931 --> 35:42.341
Who goes first?

35:54.236 --> 35:56.978
Can't let this psycho
take my goddamn eye.

36:00.325 --> 36:02.111
I know where they got
the wife and kid.

36:02.410 --> 36:05.823
It's a cabin.

36:06.748 --> 36:09.285
Probably gonna have
the whole charter there.

36:09.459 --> 36:10.539
Shit.

36:10.710 --> 36:12.416
Where is it?

36:14.506 --> 36:15.666
I'll write it down.

36:15.841 --> 36:17.377
Get him a pen and paper.

36:27.936 --> 36:29.642
I gotta say...

36:29.813 --> 36:33.271
...I'm really disappointed that
a brother was the first one to cave.

36:33.483 --> 36:34.984
TYLER:
Moses...

36:35.151 --> 36:38.109
...he give it up?
MOSES: Yeah.

36:38.280 --> 36:39.611
So we good, right?

36:42.659 --> 36:45.071
I'll let you know when we get there.

36:56.882 --> 36:58.964
Jax, I dressed Abel for school
this morning.

36:59.134 --> 37:01.500
Other than the scratch over his eye
from Thomas...

37:01.678 --> 37:04.260
...he had no cuts, no bruises,
nothing.

37:05.640 --> 37:07.892
Then what the hell happened?

37:09.644 --> 37:11.726
Why would he lie?

37:12.898 --> 37:16.561
He knew that was
gonna get you in trouble.

37:18.403 --> 37:20.564
I don't know, baby.

37:21.740 --> 37:24.231
He's been quiet, kind of distant.

37:24.409 --> 37:26.320
It's gotta be about Tara.

37:28.330 --> 37:33.120
Maybe he thinks Gemma
is trying to replace her, you know?

37:33.293 --> 37:39.209
Thinks that if he gets her out of the way,
somehow his mom comes back.

37:45.680 --> 37:47.716
He needs to talk to someone.

37:47.891 --> 37:49.347
He's 5.

37:49.517 --> 37:51.894
Doesn't need a shrink.
Well, he needs something.

37:54.522 --> 37:57.059
I mean, if he did this to himself....

37:59.194 --> 38:03.358
Wendy's right. We gotta find someone
to help him figure this shit out.

38:04.699 --> 38:06.405
JAX:
Yeah.

38:06.576 --> 38:10.160
For now,
you can't be alone with him, Mom.

38:13.041 --> 38:14.747
Jackson”.

38:15.251 --> 38:17.788
...you know I would never hurt my boy.

38:17.963 --> 38:20.670
It doesn't matter what I know.

38:20.840 --> 38:24.048
Child Services
are calling the shots now.

38:24.219 --> 38:26.881
I mean, the state could take them...

38:27.055 --> 38:28.761
...if we don't follow protocol.

38:39.776 --> 38:41.562
I'm gonna bring them to my house.

38:44.489 --> 38:46.696
I'm gonna need some help.

38:47.409 --> 38:50.401
You think you could stay with us
until we figure this out?

38:50.578 --> 38:52.864
Sleep in the nursery?

38:57.127 --> 38:58.537
Yeah, sure.

39:04.509 --> 39:06.010
Sorry, Jackie.

39:06.177 --> 39:10.796
Want us to handle this thing without you?
No. No, just give me a minute.

39:23.862 --> 39:25.853
I'm sorry, Mom.

39:32.245 --> 39:33.610
It's okay.

39:41.963 --> 39:44.625
I'll pack up their stuff.
I'll bring it by after school.

39:45.341 --> 39:46.922
Thank you.

39:47.302 --> 39:48.963
All right, let's go.

39:50.680 --> 39:52.056
WENDY:
Gem.

40:06.780 --> 40:09.112
Up here. Turn right.

40:15.997 --> 40:17.498
[DOOR OPENS]

40:32.889 --> 40:34.550
Shit.

40:36.184 --> 40:37.594
Sorry.

40:37.769 --> 40:40.681
That was a little messy.
You think?

40:45.944 --> 40:49.277
This has gotta be it.
Yeah.

40:54.744 --> 40:57.827
No Harleys. Think he was lying?

40:58.540 --> 41:00.280
I don't know.

41:19.561 --> 41:21.051
Clear it.

41:47.463 --> 41:49.078
MAN 1:
Clear!

41:58.933 --> 42:00.184
MAN 2:
House is all clear.

42:03.104 --> 42:05.095
[PHONE RINGING]

42:10.528 --> 42:12.189
Camper.

42:26.794 --> 42:27.874
[BEEPING]

42:43.645 --> 42:44.634
Ah!

43:00.495 --> 43:02.031
Hold it.

43:06.584 --> 43:08.324
[GRUNTING]

43:37.365 --> 43:39.651
Good on you, Teller.

43:42.787 --> 43:45.028
[MOSES GRUNTING]

43:47.375 --> 43:50.162
[MOSES SCREAMING]

44:06.561 --> 44:09.724
[SCREAMING]

44:19.073 --> 44:20.404
[GRUNTING]

44:41.429 --> 44:42.669
[GUNSHOTS]

45:05.411 --> 45:08.369
You sure you don't mind
getting rid of the trash?

45:08.539 --> 45:11.531
I'll keep the cars.
That'll cover my cleaning fee.

45:13.169 --> 45:14.625
Take them.

45:15.046 --> 45:17.082
Need a lift to your wheels?
No.

45:17.256 --> 45:19.087
They're just down the road.

45:22.720 --> 45:24.096
I appreciate the backup.

45:24.597 --> 45:26.303
Favor for a favor.

45:27.683 --> 45:31.096
JAX: Yeah.
Heard it was a cop who put down Leland.

45:32.230 --> 45:34.186
You set that shit up?

45:35.358 --> 45:36.438
Sort of.

45:36.984 --> 45:38.690
It don't matter.

45:38.945 --> 45:40.481
Just couldn't be me.

45:41.030 --> 45:42.645
Yeah.

45:53.084 --> 45:56.076
TIG: What the hell?
Shit.

45:56.462 --> 45:57.747
What happened to him?

45:57.922 --> 46:00.334
Couldn't get away from Moses
to give him a heads-up.

46:00.508 --> 46:03.375
We were heading out for the hospital.
He scooped up both of us.

46:03.553 --> 46:05.635
Shit.

46:06.472 --> 46:08.554
You okay?
Yeah.

46:08.724 --> 46:10.806
Couldn't cave too easy.
Took a few hits.

46:12.603 --> 46:14.434
JAX:
I'm sorry it went down that way.

46:14.605 --> 46:16.106
It's cool.

46:18.651 --> 46:20.562
Ah! Heh, heh, heh.

46:24.282 --> 46:27.069
I'm proud of you.
Thanks, man.

46:30.746 --> 46:32.828
CHIBS: Well done, brother.
Thanks.

46:36.002 --> 46:39.244
I owe you, brother. Thank you.

46:39.964 --> 46:41.579
Anything for you, Jackson.

46:44.760 --> 46:46.341
All right.

46:46.512 --> 46:47.968
I guess things went okay here?

46:48.139 --> 46:50.926
Well, we got a pile of dead black guys
in the backyard.

46:51.100 --> 46:53.307
What? Was L.A.P.D. here?

46:53.478 --> 46:55.059
[TIG CHUCKLING]

46:57.440 --> 47:00.022
There's three left if you want one.

47:00.193 --> 47:02.809
I'm good, man.
Yeah, me too.

47:10.244 --> 47:11.905
We did it.

47:13.164 --> 47:14.404
Bud. Come on.

47:14.582 --> 47:16.243
Jackie.

47:17.210 --> 47:20.668
TIG: Come on.
Yo.

47:24.217 --> 47:25.423
Pack your bags.

47:26.344 --> 47:27.880
GRANT:
What's going on?

47:28.054 --> 47:29.885
Marks's hit squad
has been discharged.

47:31.182 --> 47:34.015
What about August?
QUINN: He won't be out for a few days.

47:34.185 --> 47:38.053
We're gonna take you home, keep an eye
on you. We'll see what happens then.

47:41.817 --> 47:42.852
Okay.

47:43.027 --> 47:44.437
[LOUTREESHA SOBBING]

47:45.988 --> 47:47.444
Hey.

47:47.615 --> 47:49.276
Hey. It's okay, Mom.

47:49.450 --> 47:51.566
Hey, Mom, it's okay.

47:51.744 --> 47:53.325
Hey.

47:53.538 --> 47:55.153
We're gonna be okay.

47:56.374 --> 47:58.365
We're gonna be okay.

47:59.794 --> 48:01.159
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ON TV]

48:01.337 --> 48:05.080
WOMAN [ON TV]: I’ve waited over three years
for you, Heathcliff.

48:05.967 --> 48:09.300
MAN:
And I've waited at your gate over an hour.

48:10.638 --> 48:14.222
WOMAN:
You can be quite the scoundrel, Heathcliff.

48:16.269 --> 48:18.430
MAN:
Never, my love.

48:18.604 --> 48:21.687
We will let the horses
set the pace by our hearts...

48:21.857 --> 48:24.724
...as we become reacquainted.

48:27.613 --> 48:32.198
TU LLY: A brotherhood of misery
With smiles as sad as sighs

48:32.368 --> 48:37.203
The madness daily maddening me
And turning into agony

48:37.415 --> 48:39.781
The bliss before my eyes

48:39.959 --> 48:44.999
So stood l, in heaven's glorious sun
And in the glare of hell

48:45.172 --> 48:50.257
My spirit drank a mingled tone
Of seraph’s song, and demon 's moan

48:51.304 --> 48:57.425
What my soul bore, my soul alone
Within itself may tell

49:03.316 --> 49:04.431
Hi, darling.

49:06.068 --> 49:07.569
Hi.

49:08.863 --> 49:10.694
Rough day?

49:12.700 --> 49:14.531
What do you think?

49:18.414 --> 49:22.123
Some Aryan psycho tried to kill
one of my sheriffs.

49:24.962 --> 49:26.577
Aye.

49:29.425 --> 49:31.757
I can't do this anymore.

49:34.680 --> 49:37.763
What?
I don't know what I was thinking.

49:37.933 --> 49:40.470
Jesus, I'm an idiot.

49:41.771 --> 49:44.183
It's not you, Filip.

49:46.317 --> 49:50.777
I always put myself in these situations
where they just can't go anywhere.

49:50.946 --> 49:54.985
It's like I seek out shit
that I know is gonna crash and burn.

49:56.327 --> 50:00.070
I'm sorry,
I should've never let this happen.

50:23.729 --> 50:24.809
Okay.

50:32.405 --> 50:35.238
That's it? Okay?

50:41.539 --> 50:43.996
What do you want from me, Althea?

50:44.834 --> 50:46.745
I don't know, man.

50:46.919 --> 50:48.875
Am I right?

50:50.381 --> 50:52.588
You're a cop...

50:52.758 --> 50:54.999
...and I'm a criminal.

50:55.970 --> 50:59.212
I'm never gonna tell you
about my business.

50:59.390 --> 51:02.473
And you, sure as shit,
ain't gonna tell me yours.

51:03.018 --> 51:08.354
So no, we won't be taking strolls
down Main Street hand in hand...

51:08.524 --> 51:10.310
...picking out furniture...

51:10.735 --> 51:15.445
...and whatever other shite
normal couples do.

51:17.575 --> 51:19.440
I like you.

51:19.952 --> 51:22.238
The sex is great.

51:23.247 --> 51:27.536
And when you're not tearing apart
every single moment that we're together...

51:27.710 --> 51:30.201
...you're actually a lot of fun.

51:32.381 --> 51:34.246
But, no...

51:35.509 --> 51:38.546
...I'm not gonna make up your mind
for you.

52:15.174 --> 52:16.539
[SHIRT TEARS]

52:27.102 --> 52:28.353
[MOANS]

52:30.773 --> 52:32.013
[KNOCKING]

52:35.069 --> 52:36.559
Hey.

52:42.993 --> 52:45.325
Why are you sitting in the dark?

52:50.084 --> 52:52.370
Please turn that off.

52:52.753 --> 52:53.993
Please.

53:17.820 --> 53:19.560
What's going on?

53:20.155 --> 53:22.988
I know what this is, Alexander.

53:24.201 --> 53:25.441
Why you're with me.

53:27.162 --> 53:28.823
What are you talking about?

53:28.998 --> 53:32.536
You're a man who dares
to dance with the freaks.

53:33.919 --> 53:37.537
I perpetuate that deviance for you...

53:37.715 --> 53:41.048
...allow you to show the world
that you live outside the box.

53:42.928 --> 53:44.589
But...

53:46.348 --> 53:48.725
...I know that's where it ends for us.

53:48.893 --> 53:51.225
And I understand...

53:52.021 --> 53:56.310
...it comes with the territory
of my complicated identity.

53:59.445 --> 54:01.310
But my....

54:02.573 --> 54:07.158
My feelings for you are simpler.

54:10.372 --> 54:12.988
They live very much inside the box.

54:15.586 --> 54:17.668
I'm afraid...

54:18.047 --> 54:20.880
...Alexander, that...

54:22.134 --> 54:25.251
...I may have fallen...

54:25.512 --> 54:27.594
...in love...

54:28.182 --> 54:30.093
...with you.

54:43.530 --> 54:45.691
Um, I don't know what to say.

54:45.866 --> 54:49.029
Please, let me say it for you.

54:51.163 --> 54:53.074
I'm a man.

54:54.291 --> 54:57.909
I am a man who knows she's a woman.

54:59.797 --> 55:03.289
And that's exactly
where I'm supposed to be.

55:03.676 --> 55:06.839
That's the crisscross
that I've come to love.

55:10.140 --> 55:12.722
I don't want the surgery.

55:13.185 --> 55:15.927
I don't want to undo
what God has given me.

55:16.313 --> 55:18.349
I know how beautiful I am.

55:18.524 --> 55:20.185
You are beautiful.

55:20.359 --> 55:22.190
Thank you.

55:25.114 --> 55:28.197
I'm gonna need to put some....

55:28.450 --> 55:31.317
Some distance between us.

55:32.037 --> 55:35.200
At least until I can...

55:36.959 --> 55:39.826
...climb outside the box again.

55:42.965 --> 55:44.455
Well...

55:45.676 --> 55:48.088
...you're right, baby.

55:48.887 --> 55:51.799
About me, about everything.

55:53.559 --> 55:55.641
This is my crisscross.

55:55.811 --> 55:59.724
Because when I'm with you,
I don't have any secrets.

55:59.898 --> 56:02.025
I mean, I can't.

56:02.776 --> 56:06.769
I have to open myself up for this.

56:06.947 --> 56:08.778
And...

56:09.366 --> 56:11.527
...you see everything.

56:12.453 --> 56:14.785
All the things...

56:15.164 --> 56:20.204
...that I hide, all the shit that I hate
about myself, you see it all, baby.

56:20.919 --> 56:22.955
You see it all.

56:23.338 --> 56:26.296
And through all that, you still love me?

56:27.634 --> 56:28.794
Wow.

56:30.054 --> 56:31.214
Man...

56:31.388 --> 56:35.222
...I never had that ever
with anyone...

56:35.934 --> 56:39.301
...in any box, you know?

56:41.732 --> 56:45.145
But when I try to get close...

56:45.319 --> 56:46.900
...you know, to feel--

56:47.071 --> 56:48.652
Normal.
Yeah.

56:48.822 --> 56:51.199
Yeah.
Yes.

56:51.575 --> 56:54.362
